<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="1504" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[178,1085,1186,1237]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: distorted) refers to the distinctly asymmetric aedeagus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="1506" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[178,1085,1252,1333]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504">
Description: Small species; body length 
<quantity box="[698,821,1252,1274]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="3.8">3.8-4.7 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody: 2.0- 
<quantity box="[178,258,1281,1303]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[408,483,1281,1303]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="26.[178,218,1520,1540]" captionTargetBox="[186,1078,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-65@26.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 36-43: Micrillus distortus nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) ventral process of aedeagus in ventral view; (43) internal structure of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38- 43: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301303/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
. Coloration: head reddish-brown to dark-brown; remainder of body reddish; legs reddish-yellow; antennae reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[178,1085,1348,1487]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[248,325,1348,1370]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="26.[178,218,1520,1540]" captionTargetBox="[186,1078,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-65@26.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 36-43: Micrillus distortus nov.sp.: (36) habitus; (37) forebody; (38) male sternite VII; (39) male sternite VIII; (40-41) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (42) ventral process of aedeagus in ventral view; (43) internal structure of aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 36-37: 1.0 mm; 38- 43: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301303/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1504">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad; punctation composed of sparse micropunctation and few interspersed macropunctures; interstices with very shallow microsculpture and glossy. Eyes 0.6-0.8 times as long as postocular region and weakly projecting from lateral contours of head in dorsal view. Apical joint of maxillary palpus of conical shape and distinctly less than half the length of preapical joint.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301303" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5301303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301303/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1505" startId="26.[178,218,1520,1540]" targetBox="[186,1078,212,1484]" targetPageId="26">
